## Summary

**What changed:** `scripts/task_verification_gate.py` — the `external_only_planned()` function.

**Before:** Only recognized planned file entries containing both `"none"` AND `"gh cli"`. Failed on `"none — GitHub issue management only, no source edits"` because the comma caused `split_files` to break it into two entries, and `"no source edits"` doesn't contain `"gh cli"`.

**After:** Joins all normalized entries into one string, checks it starts with `"none"`, then checks for any of these signal keywords: `{"gh cli", "github", "issue management", "no source edits", "no code"}`. This handles comma-containing descriptions and broader non-code task descriptions.

**Tests added:**
• `"none — GitHub issue management only, no source edits"` → external-only ✅
• `"none (no source code changes, issue management only)"` → external-only ✅
• `"none (no source edits)"` → external-only ✅
• `"none"` alone (no signal) → NOT external-only ✅

**Verification:** `python3 scripts/task_verification_gate.py --test` passes all tests including the new broader patterns.

